## SECTION 9 — WRITING INSTRUCTIONS

> **POST GEN INSTRUCTION:** Follow these rules for every paragraph of body copy without exception.

- This is conversion copy — every sentence moves the buyer toward a purchase decision
- Lead with buyer benefit, not product specs — specs support the benefit, never lead
- Use buyer phrases from Section 5 naturally — "simple, lightweight, and forgiving," "I just needed something I could learn on," "salon quality at a fraction of the cost"
- Address all 5 buying objections — do not avoid them, do not hedge
- Honest cons build trust — include them, then counter with why the product is still the right buy
- Mention OFF8 discount code near ShopInlineCTA section and ShopFinalCTA area naturally — not as a standalone paragraph
- Primary keyword in `<strong>` tags every mention — no exceptions
- No editorial literary hooks — open sections with the buyer benefit or buying question directly
- H2 sections are short and direct — buyers scan, they do not read long intros
- Conclusion = final push to purchase — not a summary, a decision driver
- Internal links placed mid-post after first product CTA — anchor text natural, never forced
- No related articles section in body — handled by site component
- Language: American English — not British English
- No banned AI patterns: no "elevate," "seamlessly," "game-changing," "dive into," "transformative"
- No long em dashes — use comma or restructure sentence
- Sentence rhythm varies — short punchy sentences for key selling points, longer for context
- No "we tested" language — write informed editorial observations from specs and verified reviews only
- GEO terms near CTAs: "available for fast shipping across the USA," "ships to all US states," "free US shipping on orders over $129.99"
